==English==
===Etymology===
 It is used as modern  {{Gr.}}  word. It comes from the turkish word [[cacik]] also used in the turkish language for the same of similar forms of tzatziki.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''tzatziki'''
# a [[Greek]] [[starter]] made from [[yoghurt]], [[cucumber]], [[garlic]], [[olive oil]], [[dill]] or [[mint]]; usually served with [[pitta bread]] and as a [[meze]]